			<h1>BAYADA Hospice, Vermont and New Hampshire Region - Norwich, VT</h1>

			<p>Serving the Upper Valley, our office—located just across from Dan and Whit’s on Main Street—provides the highest quality <a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#Hospice">hospice</a> services to people throughout Vermont and along the river in New Hampshire.  Please visit our <a href="services-hospice.asp" target="_blank">Hospice Services</a> page to learn more about how we can help.</p>
			<p>All care is provided with compassion, excellence, and reliability—our core values. We also have teams conveniently located throughout the state, so no matter where you or your loved ones may reside, we will be able to provide the services you need.</p>

			<h2>Experienced hospice team</h2>
			<p>Our experienced professionals are caring members of your community who are focused entirely on hospice care. Director Jessica DeGrechie and her team are passionate about helping people at end-of-life have comfort, grace, and dignity</p>

			<h2>Our dedicated office team includes:</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Clinical Manager</li>
					<li>Client Services Manager</li>
					<li>Bereavement Coordinator</li>
					<li>Volunteer Coordinator</li>
					<li>Psychosocial Services Manager</li>
					<li>Associate</li>
					<li>Community Liaison</li>
				</ul><br>

			<h2>Volunteers</h2>
			<p>In addition to our office and field teams, volunteers make an important difference in the lives of our patients and their families. Some provide companionship, run errands, or help with other tasks. But no matter what they do, they are a gift! If you or someone you know would like to volunteer with us, please let Nancy know. We provide a flexible training and orientation schedule to meet your needs.</p>

			<h2>Bereavement program</h2>
			<p>We know how difficult it can be to lose a loved one, and we provide help and support in many different ways. For example, non-denominational memorial services are held during holiday seasons to help people remember loved ones and be supported in their grief during a difficult time of year. Ask us about our bereavement program to learn more.</p>

